{
  "stem": "14897.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "A few people, of whom I was one, who would go in the morning, in the worst weather, and strip and wash, so I guess I must have had a towel or something to dry with.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, you know, there's a bathroom.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It took me months to be able to use the bathroom alone.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I just was not used to any privacy.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Things that are so normal that you lose-- so walking the street of Paris, in a way, you think that when it's over, jubilation.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But it's not.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Because very few people were lucky enough to go immediately-- to be saved and go immediately to normal life.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And even when you do go to normal life, it is hard to adapt.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I, personally, was not consumed by guilt, which I know is the experience of many survivors.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But-- but you have a feeling of inferiority because you-- you don't belong with normal people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It takes a long time to get used to it, to overcome it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, no, you feel that way because you don't have the things that other people have, because you are living in a-- in a dormitory, and you don't own a change of clothes, and you don't-- you're not going to school.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You're not living the normal life of other people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Fortunately, we were in France a rather short period of time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because in Palestine, at the time, there was a quota for how many Jews could immigrate every year.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the quota for 1945 was empty.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was no place from which Jews could immigrate.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So being one of the first, the Joint Committee arranged for us official papers to go to-- to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
